(13, NULL, 'PINK BEACH', '<div class=\"beach__body\">\n							<div class=\"beach__about\">\n								<p class=\"beach__about-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">\n									ENDLESS VIBRANT HUES IN INDONESIA								</p>\n								<p class=\"beach__about-text\">\n									The striking pink hue of its sand is what sets Pink Beach apart as one of the most unique beaches in the world. The rare pink color is caused by the mixture of white sand with red coral fragments. This distinctive coloration makes it a visual standout and a popular spot for photography. The beach is part of a protected area within Komodo National Park, which helps maintain its pristine condition and supports a rich marine biodiversity, making it also ideal for snorkeling and diving. Visitors come to enjoy the calm, clear waters and take in the scenic views of the surrounding rugged islands, which change colors with the seasons. Pink Beach is not just a beach; it\'s a gateway to exploring the broader natural wonders of Komodo National Park.	\n								</p>\n							</div>\n							<div class=\"beach__image\">\n								<img src=\"https://worlds50beaches.com/assets/images/maps/map-2025-13.jpg\" alt=\"map\">\n							</div>\n						</div>\n', ' <div class=\"container\"> 					<div class=\"more\"> 						<div class=\"more__item\"> 							<p class=\"more__item-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\"> 								Pink Beach WEATHER AVERAGES 							</p> 							<table class=\"weather__table\"> 								<thead> 									<tr> 										<td class=\"first__cell\"></td> 										<td>AVG. HIGH</td> 										<td>AVG. LOW</td> 										<td>RAINY DAYS</td> 									</tr> 								</thead> 								<tbody> 									<tr> 										<td class=\"first__cell\">JANUARY</td> 										<td> 											<span>30</span> 											° 										</td> 										<td> 											<span>25</span> 											° 										</td> 										<td>16.9</td> 									</tr> 									<tr> 										<td class=\"first__cell\">FEBRUARY</td> 										