(43, NULL, 'NUDEY BEACH', '<div class=\"beach__body\">\n                                                        <div class=\"beach__about\">\n                                                                <p class=\"beach__about-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">\n                                                                        UNTOUCHED SECLUSION IN LUSH AUSTRALIAN RAINFOREST                                                                </p>\n                                                                <p class=\"beach__about-text\">\n                                                                        Nudey Beach is consistently ranked among Australia\'s most beautiful beaches. Located on Fitzroy Island off the coast of Queensland, it is often considered the gateway to the Great Barrier Reef. Surrounded by lush tropical rainforest, the beach offers a picturesque, untouched, and secluded setting. Accessible by a short boat ride or a scenic hike from the island\'s main area, getting to the beach is part of the experience itself. Granite boulders scattered along the shore add a unique twist, while the shallow reef provides magical snorkeling opportunities. The warm waters make it a great year-round destination, perfect for enjoying Australia’s natural beauty at any time of year.        \n                                                                </p>\n                                                        </div>\n                                                        <div class=\"beach__image\">\n                                                                <img src=\"https://worlds50beaches.com/assets/images/maps/map-2025-37.jpg\" alt=\"map\">\n                                                        </div>\n                                                </div>', ' <div class=\"container\">                                         <div class=\"more\">                                                 <div class=\"more__item\">        