(49, NULL, 'KURAMATHI SAND BANK', '<div class=\"beach__body\">\n                                                        <div class=\"beach__about\">\n                                                                <p class=\"beach__about-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">\n                                                                        THE BEST THE MALDIVES HAS TO OFFER                                                                </p>\n                                                                <p class=\"beach__about-text\">\n                                                                        While the Maldives is known for its incredible beaches, Kuramathi Sand Bank stands out. Many beaches in the Maldives are artificial, but Kuramathi is an entirely natural island. Located in the beautiful Rasdhoo Atoll, it is more accessible from Malé by boat or seaplane. The surroundings feature all the quintessential elements of a perfect Maldivian beach—powder-soft sand and shallow waters—but the unique experience of entering the sand bank sets it apart from others. Depending on the tides, visitors can wander far out into the crystal-clear sea, often spotting amazing marine life, such as stingrays and nurse sharks. Kuramathi Sand Bank is also an ideal spot to catch a stunning sunset. Additionally, unlike the more expensive private islands in the region, Kuramathi is a more accessible option for travelers.        \n                                                                </p>\n                                                        </div>\n                                                        <div class=\"beach__image\">\n                                                                <img src=\"https://worlds50beaches.com/assets/images/maps/map-2025-49.jpg\" alt=\"map\">\n                                                        </div>\n                                                </div>', ' <div class=\"container\">                     