(51, NULL, 'HA LONG BAY', '<div class=\"beach__body\">\n    <div class=\"beach__about\">\n        <p class=\"beach__about-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">\n            AN ANCIENT KARST SEA OF THOUSANDS OF ISLETS\n        </p>\n        <p class=\"beach__about-text\">\n            Ha Long Bay is one of the planet’s most extraordinary coastal landscapes — a sprawling karst seascape dotted with thousands of limestone islets, sea stacks and hidden coves rising from emerald waters. Recognized as a UNESCO World Heritage Site, the bay combines dramatic geology, rich biodiversity and a living cultural heritage preserved in its floating fishing villages. Visitors explore Ha Long by cruising traditional wooden junks or modern yachts, visiting spectacular caves such as Sung Sot (Surprise Cave), kayaking into quiet lagoons, and watching the sunrise and sunset cast golden light across the karst towers. Each island and cavern tells a story shaped over millions of years, making Ha Long both a place of scientific wonder and timeless beauty — where nature and local life meet on the water.\n        </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"beach__image\">\n        <img src=\"https://worlds50beaches.com/assets/images/maps/map-2025-01.jpg\" alt=\"map\">\n    </div>\n</div>', ' <div class=\"container\">     <div class=\"more\">       <div class=\"more__item\">         <p class=\"more__item-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">           HA LONG BAY WEATHER AVERAGES         </p>         <table class=\"weather__table\">           <thead>             <tr>               <td class=\"first__cell\"></td>               <td>AVG. HIGH</td>               <td>AVG. LOW</td>               <td>RAINY DAYS</td>             </tr>           </thead>           <tbody>             <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JAN</td><td><span>20</span>°</td><td><span>13</span>°</td><td>10</td></tr>             <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">FEB</td><td><span>20</span>°</td><td><span>14</span>°</td><td>11</td></tr>             <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">MAR</td><td><span>23</span>°</td><td><span>17</span>°</td><td>13</td></tr>             <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">APR</td><td><span>27</span>°</td><td><span>21</span>°</td><td>13</td></tr>             <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">MAY</td><td><span>31</span>°</td><td><span>24</span>°</td><td>14</td></tr>             <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JUN</td><td><span>32</span>°</td><td><span>25</span>°</td><td>15</td></tr>             <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JUL</td><td><span>32</span>°</td><td><span>26</span>°</td><td>15</td></tr>             <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">AUG</td><td><span>32</span>°</td><td><span>25</span>°</td><td>16</td></tr>             <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">SEP</td><td><span>31</span>°</td><td><span>24</span>°</td><td>14</td></tr>             <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">OCT</td><td><span>29</span>°</td><td><span>21</span>°</td><td>11</td></tr>             <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">NOV</td><td><span>25</span>°</td><td><span>17</span>°</td><td>8</td></tr>             <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">DEC</td><td><span>22</span>°</td><td><span>14</span>°</td><td>7</td></tr>           </tbody>         </table>                </div>       <div class=\"more__item more__item-right\">         <div class=\"more__info\">           <p class=\"more__info-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">             THE PERFECT DAY IN HA LONG BAY           </p>           <ul class=\"more__info-list\">             <li>               <p><b>WIND & SEA CONDITIONS</b></p>               <p>Choose early morning or late afternoon to avoid strong winds - the sea is calmer and perfect for kayaking or exploring caves.</p>             </li>             <li>               <p><b>SEASONS</b></p>               <p>Spring (Mar–Apr) and autumn (Sep–Oct) have the most pleasant weather, clear skies, ideal for sightseeing and photography.</p>             </li>             <li>               <p><b>CALM SEAS</b></p>               <p>Oct–Dec is dry and cool with calm waters—perfect for cruising and outdoor activities.</p>             </li>             <li>               <p><b>BEST HOURS</b></p>               <p>Early morning and late afternoon offer the best lighting for sunrise or sunset, with fewer tourists and beautiful, soft light.</p>             </li>           </ul>         </div>       </div>     </div> </div>', 'https://www.agoda.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Featured-image-Halong-Bay-Vietnam.jpg', 37),
(52, NULL, 'PHU QUOC ISLAND', '<div class=\"beach__body\">\n  <div class=\"beach__about\">\n    <p class=\"beach__about-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">\n      VIETNAM’S TROPICAL PARADISE OF BELLETS AND BIODIVERSITY\n    </p>\n    <p class=\"beach__about-text\">\n      Phu Quoc Island, known as Vietnam’s “Pearl Island,” is a tropical sanctuary in the Gulf of Thailand. It boasts pristine white-sand beaches, turquoise waters, dense jungle in its interior and a vibrant marine ecosystem. Rising quickly in popularity, it features luxurious resorts, traditional fishing villages and a UNESCO-recognized biosphere reserve. Whether you prefer tranquil beach days, snorkeling in coral reefs, exploring waterfalls or indulging in local seafood markets—Phu Quoc offers a rich mix of luxury, nature and authentic island culture.\n    </p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"beach__image\">\n    <img src=\"https://worlds50beaches.com/assets/images/maps/map-2025-01.jpg\" alt=\"map\">\n  </div>\n</div>', ' <div class=\"container\">     <div class=\"more\">         <div class=\"more__item\">           <p class=\"more__item-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">             PHU QUOC WEATHER AVERAGES           </p>           <table class=\"weather__table\">             <thead>               <tr>                 <td class=\"first__cell\"></td>                 <td>AVG. HIGH (°C)</td>                 <td>AVG. LOW (°C)</td>                 <td>RAIN (MM)</td>                 <td>RAINY DAYS</td>               </tr>             </thead>             <tbody>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JAN</td><td>30.8</td><td>23.9</td><td>34</td><td>5</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">FEB</td><td>31.4</td><td>24.1</td><td>29</td><td>4</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">MAR</td><td>32.2</td><td>25.3</td><td>55</td><td>6</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">APR</td><td>32.7</td><td>25.9</td><td>149</td><td>12</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">MAY</td><td>32.1</td><td>26.5</td><td>298</td><td>20</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JUN</td><td>31.0</td><td>26.3</td><td>415</td><td>22</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JUL</td><td>30.0</td><td>26.0</td><td>420</td><td>22</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">AUG</td><td>29.9</td><td>26.1</td><td>546</td><td>24</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">SEP</td><td>29.8</td><td>25.6</td><td>473</td><td>22</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">OCT</td><td>30.6</td><td>25.0</td><td>387</td><td>22</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">NOV</td><td>31.3</td><td>25.1</td><td>169</td><td>13</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">DEC</td><td>30.9</td><td>24.4</td><td>59</td><td>6</td></tr>             </tbody>           </table>         </div>         <div class=\"more__item more__item-right\">           <div class=\"more__info\">             <p class=\"more__info-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">               THE PERFECT DAY IN PHU QUOC             </p>             <ul class=\"more__info-list\">               <li>                 <p><b>DRY SEASON CONDITIONS</b></p>                 <p>The best time is December to March: sunny skies, calm seas and warm air perfect for snorkeling, swimming, and beach lounging. :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>SHOULDER MONTHS</b></p>                 <p>April to June brings warm temperatures (~28–35 °C) with fewer crowds and lower prices—great for a balance of weather and value. :contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>RAINY SEASON BENEFITS</b></p>                 <p>May to October sees more rain and rougher seas, but offers lush green landscapes, quieter beaches, and discounted rates. :contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>BEST HOURS</b></p>                 <p>Early morning and late afternoon offer the most comfortable light and fewer tourists—ideal for beaches, photography, and island exploration.</p>               </li>             </ul>           </div>         </div>     </div> </div>', 'https://discoveryindochina.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Phu-Quoc-Island-1000.jpg', 38),
(53, NULL, 'DA NANG BEACH', '<div class=\"beach__body\">\n  <div class=\"beach__about\">\n    <p class=\"beach__about-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">\n      SUN-KISSED SHORES AT THE HEART OF CENTRAL VIETNAM\n    </p>\n    <p class=\"beach__about-text\">\n      Da Nang’s beaches—like the famous My Khe and Non Nuoc—offer golden sands, warm waves, and sweeping ocean views. Nicknamed “Vietnam’s Miami,” the city combines beach fun with city vibes, coastal hills, and cultural attractions. From sunbathing and water sports to exploring Son Tra Peninsula and nearby heritage sites, Da Nang offers a diverse seaside experience for all types of travelers.\n    </p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"beach__image\">\n    <img src=\"https://worlds50beaches.com/assets/images/maps/map-2025-01.jpg\" alt=\"map\">\n  </div>\n</div>', ' <div class=\"container\">     <div class=\"more\">         <div class=\"more__item\">           <p class=\"more__item-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">             DA NANG WEATHER AVERAGES           </p>           <table class=\"weather__table\">             <thead>               <tr>                 <td class=\"first__cell\"></td>                 <td>AVG. HIGH (°C)</td>                 <td>AVG. LOW (°C)</td>                 <td>RAIN PATTERN</td>               </tr>             </thead>             <tbody>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Jan–Feb</td><td>≈22–25</td><td>≈18–20</td><td>Dry</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Mar–May</td><td>25–30</td><td>≈20–25</td><td>Low rain</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Jun–Aug</td><td>30–33</td><td>≈25–27</td><td>Hot, sunny</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Sep–Dec</td><td>25–30</td><td>≈22–25</td><td>Rainy / typhoon risk</td></tr>             </tbody>           </table>                   </div>         <div class=\"more__item more__item-right\">           <div class=\"more__info\">             <p class=\"more__info-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">               THE PERFECT DAY AT DA NANG BEACH             </p>             <ul class=\"more__info-list\">               <li>                 <p><b>BEST SEASON</b></p>                 <p>April to August offers warm, sunny weather ideal for swimming and seaside activities :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}.</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>SHOULDER MONTHS</b></p>                 <p>March–May is especially pleasant—sunny with moderate temperatures and low rain — perfect for beach visits with fewer crowds :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}.</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>AVOID</b></p>                 <p>September to December bring heavy rain and possible storms—best suited for calmer sightseeing rather than beach fun :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}.</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>TIME OF DAY</b></p>                 <p>Early morning or late afternoon provides softer light, cooler temperatures, and less sun for a more comfortable beach experience.</p>               </li>             </ul>           </div>         </div>     </div> </div>', 'https://blisshoian.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/My-Khe-Beach-Da-Nang-2023-Vietnamnomad.webp', 39),
(54, NULL, 'NHA TRANG BEACH', '<div class=\"beach__body\">\n  <div class=\"beach__about\">\n    <p class=\"beach__about-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">\n      CENTRAL VIETNAM’S SERENE SEAFRONT WITH ISLAND VIEWS\n    </p>\n    <p class=\"beach__about-text\">\n      Nha Trang is famous for its long, sandy shoreline and crystal-clear waters, framed by gentle mountains and nearby islands. Recognized by Travel + Leisure as one of the most beautiful bays in the world :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}, it blends laid-back beach life with vibrant local culture—from island hopping and snorkeling to dining and night markets along the coastal promenade.\n    </p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"beach__image\">\n    <img src=\"https://worlds50beaches.com/assets/images/maps/map-2025-01.jpg\" alt=\"map\">\n  </div>\n</div>', ' <div class=\"container\">     <div class=\"more\">         <div class=\"more__item\">           <p class=\"more__item-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">             NHA TRANG WEATHER AVERAGES           </p>           <table class=\"weather__table\">             <thead>               <tr>                 <td class=\"first__cell\"></td>                 <td>AVG. HIGH (°C)</td>                 <td>AVG. LOW (°C)</td>                 <td>RAIN (MM)</td>                 <td>RAINY DAYS</td>               </tr>             </thead>             <tbody>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JAN</td><td>27</td><td>21.7</td><td>40</td><td>8</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">FEB</td><td>28</td><td>22</td><td>15</td><td>4</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">MAR</td><td>29.4</td><td>23.3</td><td>30</td><td>3</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">APR</td><td>31.1</td><td>25</td><td>35</td><td>4</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">MAY</td><td>32.4</td><td>25.8</td><td>70</td><td>8</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JUN</td><td>32.7</td><td>26.1</td><td>60</td><td>9</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JUL</td><td>32.5</td><td>25.9</td><td>35</td><td>8</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">AUG</td><td>32.7</td><td>25.9</td><td>50</td><td>10</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">SEP</td><td>31.8</td><td>25.2</td><td>160</td><td>15</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">OCT</td><td>30</td><td>24.4</td><td>300</td><td>18</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">NOV</td><td>28.6</td><td>23.6</td><td>330</td><td>18</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">DEC</td><td>27.3</td><td>22.6</td><td>155</td><td>14</td></tr>             </tbody>           </table>                    </div>         <div class=\"more__item more__item-right\">           <div class=\"more__info\">             <p class=\"more__info-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">               THE PERFECT DAY IN NHA TRANG             </p>             <ul class=\"more__info-list\">               <li>                 <p><b>BEST TIME FOR BEACH</b></p>                 <p>February to April offers moderate temps (~26–27 °C), minimal rainfall—ideal for swimming, island hopping and snorkeling :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}.</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>DIVING & WATER ACTIVITIES</b></p>                 <p>April to August gives best water clarity and marine life visibility—perfect for diving enthusiasts :contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}.</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>QUIETER, BUDGET-FRIENDLY MONTHS</b></p>                 <p>September to December sees more rain but fewer crowds and lower rates. Rain tends to be heavy but short-lived :contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}.</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>IDEAL HOURS</b></p>                 <p>Early mornings and late afternoons offer beautiful light and calm sea conditions—best for photos and leisurely walks.</p>               </li>             </ul>           </div>         </div>     </div> </div>', 'https://static.vinwonders.com/production/nha-trang-bay-banner.jpg', 40),
(55, NULL, 'PHAN RANG BEACH', '<div class=\"beach__body\">\n  <div class=\"beach__about\">\n    <p class=\"beach__about-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">\n      A WIND-KISSED COASTLINE WHERE CULTURE MEETS THE SEA\n    </p>\n    <p class=\"beach__about-text\">\n      Phan Rang Beach lies along Vietnam’s driest coastline—named literally “Wind & Sun”—offering long stretches of sandy shore blessed with consistent sunshine and strong coastal breezes. It’s emerging as a stellar spot for kitesurfing, with pristine lagoons like My Hoa and wide-open bays like Ninh Chu that deliver thrilling wind and wave conditions. Beyond adrenaline, it’s also rich in Cham cultural heritage, nearby vineyards, and a laid-back coastal charm.\n    </p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"beach__image\">\n    <img src=\"https://worlds50beaches.com/assets/images/maps/map-2025-01.jpg\" alt=\"map\">\n  </div>\n</div>', ' <div class=\"container\">     <div class=\"more\">         <div class=\"more__item\">           <p class=\"more__item-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">             PHAN RANG WEATHER AVERAGES           </p>           <table class=\"weather__table\">             <thead>               <tr>                 <td class=\"first__cell\"></td>                 <td>AVG. HIGH (°C)</td>                 <td>AVG. LOW (°C)</td>                 <td>RAIN (MM)</td>                 <td>RAINY DAYS</td>               </tr>             </thead>             <tbody>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Jan</td><td>27</td><td>20.7</td><td>24</td><td>2</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Feb</td><td>28.7</td><td>20.8</td><td>9</td><td>1</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Mar</td><td>30.4</td><td>22.4</td><td>24</td><td>3</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Apr</td><td>31.8</td><td>24.2</td><td>42</td><td>6</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">May</td><td>32</td><td>25.2</td><td>120</td><td>13</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Jun</td><td>32</td><td>25.2</td><td>90</td><td>11</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Jul</td><td>32</td><td>25.1</td><td>85</td><td>10</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Aug</td><td>32.1</td><td>25</td><td>85</td><td>11</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Sep</td><td>30.7</td><td>24.5</td><td>189</td><td>16</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Oct</td><td>28.8</td><td>23.6</td><td>219</td><td>16</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Nov</td><td>27.9</td><td>22.9</td><td>147</td><td>10</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Dec</td><td>26.8</td><td>21.7</td><td>111</td><td>7</td></tr>             </tbody>           </table>                    </div>         <div class=\"more__item more__item-right\">           <div class=\"more__info\">             <p class=\"more__info-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">               THE PERFECT DAY IN PHAN RANG BEACH             </p>             <ul class=\"more__info-list\">               <li>                 <p><b>BEST SEASON</b></p>                 <p>April to August brings stable dry weather—ideal for sun, beach activities, and kitesurfing.</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>KITESURFING SEASON</b></p>                 <p>December to March gives the strongest winds (20–40 kt) at My Hoa Lagoon; March–September is still viable at Ninh Chu Bay. :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>RAIN RISKS</b></p>                 <p>Avoid September–November due to higher rainfall and possible storms—visit instead during dry periods.</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>IDEAL HOURS</b></p>                 <p>Afternoon sees the best wind for kitesurfing; mornings are calmer and perfect for relaxing or exploring nearby cultural sites.</p>               </li>             </ul>           </div>         </div>     </div> </div>', 'https://pystravel.vn/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fbooking.pystravel.vn%2Fuploads%2Fposts%2Favatar%2F1744011744.jpg&w=3840&q=75', 41),
(56, NULL, 'VUNG TAU BEACH', '<div class=\"beach__body\">\n  <div class=\"beach__about\">\n    <p class=\"beach__about-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">\n      A COASTAL CITY WHERE BEACH LIFE MEETS EASY ACCESS\n    </p>\n    <p class=\"beach__about-text\">\n      Just over 2 hours from Ho Chi Minh City, Vung Tau offers sandy beaches like Front Beach and Back Beach framed by green hills, local seafood stalls, and historic landmarks. Known as the \"coastal gateway of the south\", it balances beach relaxation with cultural sites such as the Christ the King statue and Thích Ca Phật Đài temple. While crowds and beach cleanliness can vary, places like Ho Tram Beach and Pineapple Beach offer more serene experiences away from the city.:contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}\n    </p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"beach__image\">\n    <img src=\"https://worlds50beaches.com/assets/images/maps/map-2025-01.jpg\" alt=\"map\">\n  </div>\n</div>', ' <div class=\"container\">     <div class=\"more\">         <div class=\"more__item\">           <p class=\"more__item-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">             VUNG TAU WEATHER AVERAGES           </p>           <table class=\"weather__table\">             <thead>               <tr>                 <td class=\"first__cell\"></td>                 <td>DRY SEASON (Nov–Apr)</td>                 <td>RAINY SEASON (May–Oct)</td>               </tr>             </thead>             <tbody>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Avg. Temp</td><td>22–30 °C</td><td>25–32 °C</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Rainfall</td><td>Low</td><td>Moderate, peaking Oct ~236 mm</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Best For</td><td>Beach, water sports, sunshine</td><td>Fewer crowds, surfing, budget travel</td></tr>             </tbody>           </table>         </div>         <div class=\"more__item more__item-right\">           <div class=\"more__info\">             <p class=\"more__info-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">               THE PERFECT DAY IN VUNG TAU             </p>             <ul class=\"more__info-list\">               <li>                 <p><b>DRY SEASON (Nov–Apr)</b></p>                 <p>Sunny, calm seas—ideal for surfing, coastal hikes, island tours like Front and Back Beach. Peak travel months: Feb–Mar.:contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>OFF-PEAK WET SEASON (May–Oct)</b></p>                 <p>Short showers, less crowded beaches, lower prices—surfing conditions may improve along stretches like Ho Tram.:contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>AVOID</b></p>                 <p>October brings heavy rains, rough seas—exercise safety caution for swimming.:contentReference[oaicite:6]{index=6}</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>BEST TIMES OF DAY</b></p>                 <p>Early morning or late afternoon offers softer light, cooler temps, and calmer water—great for walks, photos, and dining by the sea.</p>               </li>             </ul>           </div>         </div>     </div> </div>', 'https://vietnamdiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Vung-Tau-beach.jpg', 42),
(57, NULL, 'PHAN THIET BEACH  ', '<div class=\"beach__body\">\n  <div class=\"beach__about\">\n    <p class=\"beach__about-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">\n      TRADITIONAL BEACH TOWN BLENDING SUN, SEA & CULTURE\n    </p>\n    <p class=\"beach__about-text\">\n      Phan Thiet is a coastal city that offers long sandy beaches, warm climate, and easy access to the famed sand dunes of Mũi Né. It supports a thriving tourism scene with resorts, seafood markets, and water sports, especially kite surfing and windsurfing during windy dry seasons :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}.\n    </p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"beach__image\">\n    <img src=\"https://worlds50beaches.com/assets/images/maps/map-2025-01.jpg\" alt=\"map\">\n  </div>\n</div>', ' <div class=\"container\">     <div class=\"more\">         <div class=\"more__item\">           <p class=\"more__item-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">             PHAN THIET WEATHER AVERAGES           </p>           <table class=\"weather__table\">             <thead>               <tr>                 <td class=\"first__cell\"></td>                 <td>AVG. HIGH (°C)</td>                 <td>AVG. LOW (°C)</td>                 <td>RAIN (MM)</td>                 <td>RAINY DAYS</td>               </tr>             </thead>             <tbody>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JAN</td><td>29.8</td><td>22.4</td><td>1</td><td>0</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">FEB</td><td>30.0</td><td>22.6</td><td>0</td><td>0</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">MAR</td><td>31.2</td><td>24.3</td><td>6</td><td>1</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">APR</td><td>32.5</td><td>25.8</td><td>30</td><td>4</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">MAY</td><td>33.2</td><td>26.4</td><td>135</td><td>13</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JUN</td><td>32.6</td><td>25.7</td><td>145</td><td>16</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JUL</td><td>31.9</td><td>25.2</td><td>165</td><td>16</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">AUG</td><td>31.8</td><td>25.2</td><td>165</td><td>18</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">SEP</td><td>31.9</td><td>25.1</td><td>190</td><td>17</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">OCT</td><td>31.4</td><td>24.7</td><td>155</td><td>14</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">NOV</td><td>31.2</td><td>24.2</td><td>60</td><td>7</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">DEC</td><td>30.4</td><td>23.2</td><td>20</td><td>3</td></tr>             </tbody>           </table>                   </div>         <div class=\"more__item more__item-right\">           <div class=\"more__info\">             <p class=\"more__info-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">               THE PERFECT DAY IN PHAN THIET             </p>             <ul class=\"more__info-list\">               <li>                 <p><b>BEST SEASON</b></p>                 <p>December to April—dry, pleasantly warm, and ideal for beach outings, water sports, and dune adventures :contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}.</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>KITESURFING SEASON</b></p>                 <p>Stronger coastal breezes from November to April make Mui Ne a top spot for kite surfing and wind sports :contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}.</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>OFF-PEAK WITH NATURE’S LUSHNESS</b></p>                 <p>May to October brings sporadic rain that refreshes the landscape—great for solo travelers and budget stays :contentReference[oaicite:6]{index=6}.</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>BEST HOURS</b></p>                 <p>Early morning offers soft light and calm seas for relaxing strolls; late afternoon brings pleasant breezes perfect for beach walks and photo ops.</p>               </li>             </ul>           </div>         </div>     </div> </div>', 'https://tourphanthiet.com.vn/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Quan-bar-Chameleon-phan-thiet.jpeg', 43);
