(58, NULL, 'CUA LO BEACH', '<div class=\"beach__body\">\n<div class=\"beach__about\">\n<p class=\"beach__about-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">\nA PINE-LINED SEAFRONT WITH SOFT SAND & LOCAL LIFE\n</p>\n<p class=\"beach__about-text\">\nCua Lo Beach stretches along the Gulf of Tonkin just east of Vinh city — a long, gently sloping shoreline framed by casuarina (pine) trees, clear shallow water and small offshore islets (Hòn Ngư, Hòn Chù, Hòn Mắt). The area combines seaside leisure with authentic local culture: fresh seafood markets, traditional fishing activities and nearby temples. Visitors enjoy swimming, coastal walks at sunrise, sampling grilled fish specialties, and short island trips. Compared with more crowded southern beaches, Cua Lo keeps a relaxed, regional charm while offering accessible facilities and expanding coastal tourism.\n</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"beach__image\">\n<img src=\"https://worlds50beaches.com/assets/images/maps/map-2025-01.jpg\" alt=\"map\">\n</div>\n</div>', ' <div class=\"container\">     <div class=\"more\">         <div class=\"more__item\">             <p class=\"more__item-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">                 CUA LO WEATHER AVERAGES             </p>             <table class=\"weather__table\">                 <thead>                     <tr>                         <td class=\"first__cell\"></td>                         <td>AVG. HIGH (°C)</td>                         <td>AVG. LOW (°C)</td>                         <td>RAINY DAYS</td>                     </tr>                 </thead>                 <tbody>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JANUARY</td><td><span>21.0</span>°</td><td><span>14.0</span>°</td><td>6</td></tr>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">FEBRUARY</td><td><span>21.4</span>°</td><td><span>14.4</span>°</td><td>6</td></tr>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">MARCH</td><td><span>23.9</span>°</td><td><span>16.9</span>°</td><td>8</td></tr>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">APRIL</td><td><span>27.6</span>°</td><td><span>20.6</span>°</td><td>10</td></tr>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">MAY</td><td><span>31.2</span>°</td><td><span>24.2</span>°</td><td>12</td></tr>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JUNE</td><td><span>32.9</span>°</td><td><span>25.9</span>°</td><td>14</td></tr>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JULY</td><td><span>33.2</span>°</td><td><span>26.2</span>°</td><td>16</td></tr>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">AUGUST</td><td><span>32.2</span>°</td><td><span>25.2</span>°</td><td>20</td></tr>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">SEPTEMBER</td><td><span>30.4</span>°</td><td><span>23.4</span>°</td><td>16</td></tr>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">OCTOBER</td><td><span>28.0</span>°</td><td><span>21.0</span>°</td><td>14</td></tr>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">NOVEMBER</td><td><span>25.0</span>°</td><td><span>18.0</span>°</td><td>10</td></tr>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">DECEMBER</td><td><span>22.2</span>°</td><td><span>15.2</span>°</td><td>7</td></tr>                 </tbody>             </table>                     </div>         <div class=\"more__item more__item-right\">             <div class=\"more__info\">                 <p class=\"more__info-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">                     THE PERFECT DAY AT CUA LO                 </p>                 <ul class=\"more__info-list\">                     <li>                         <p><b>BEST SEASONS</b></p>                         <p>February–April: mild temperatures and relatively low rain — ideal for swimming, island trips and sunrise walks.</p>                     </li>                     <li>                         <p><b>PEAK SUMMER</b></p>                         <p>May–August brings warm weather and beach-friendly days but also more afternoon showers; plan morning activities for clearer skies.</p>                     </li>                     <li>                         <p><b>QUIETER, GREEN SEASON</b></p>                         <p>September–November receives heavier rainfall (spectacular skies), fewer crowds and lower rates — good if you prefer quieter visits and dramatic coastal landscapes.</p>                     </li>                     <li>                         <p><b>TIME OF DAY</b></p>                         <p>Sunrise along the pine-lined shore is the most peaceful and photogenic time; late afternoon brings softer light and cooler breezes for dining outdoors.</p>                     </li>                 </ul>             </div>         </div>     </div> </div>', 'https://nads.1cdn.vn/2024/11/08/W_image003.jpg', 44),
(59, NULL, 'DO SON BEACH', '<div class=\"beach__body\">\n    <div class=\"beach__about\">\n        <p class=\"beach__about-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">\n            A SCENIC SANCTUARY WITH CALM WATERS & FESTIVAL VIBRANCY\n        </p>\n        <p class=\"beach__about-text\">\n            Do Son Beach, about 20 km from central Hai Phong, offers soft golden sands lined with casuarina trees and calm seas—perfect for summer escapes and water sports. It doubles as a cultural hub, hosting festivals like the buffalo fighting festival, while offering local seafood, lighthouse views, and easy access to nearby Cat Ba and Bach Long Vĩ islands.\n        </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"beach__image\">\n        <img src=\"https://worlds50beaches.com/assets/images/maps/map-2025-01.jpg\" alt=\"map\">\n    </div>\n</div>', ' <div class=\"container\">     <div class=\"more\">         <div class=\"more__item\">             <p class=\"more__item-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">                 DO SON WEATHER AVERAGES             </p>             <table class=\"weather__table\">                 <thead>                     <tr>                         <td class=\"first__cell\"></td>                         <td>AVG HIGH (°C)</td>                         <td>AVG LOW (°C)</td>                         <td>RAIN (mm)</td>                     </tr>                 </thead>                 <tbody>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">JAN–FEB</td><td>20</td><td>14</td><td>low</td></tr>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">MAR–APR</td><td>23–27</td><td>18–22</td><td>moderate</td></tr>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">MAY–JUL</td><td>30–33</td><td>24–26</td><td>high</td></tr>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">AUG</td><td>31.5</td><td>25.3</td><td>~473</td></tr>                     <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">OCT–NOV</td><td>28–25</td><td>22–18</td><td>decreasing</td></tr>                 </tbody>             </table>         </div>         <div class=\"more__item more__item-right\">             <div class=\"more__info\">                 <p class=\"more__info-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">                     THE PERFECT DAY AT DO SON                 </p>                 <ul class=\"more__info-list\">                     <li>                         <p><b>BEST SEASONS</b></p>                         <p>Spring (Mar–Apr) and autumn (Oct–Nov): mild, less rain — great for beach walks and outdoor festivals. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}</p>                     </li>                     <li>                         <p><b>SUMMER</b></p>                         <p>May–July brings beach weather but expect heavy rain, especially in August. :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}</p>                     </li>                     <li>                         <p><b>WINTER</b></p>                         <p>Jan–Feb can be cool and dry — not ideal for swimming but peaceful and clear. :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}</p>                     </li>                     <li>                         <p><b>TIME OF DAY</b></p>                         <p>Early morning offers calm sea and light breeze—perfect for strolling; late afternoon brings softer light and sea breeze. :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}</p>                     </li>                 </ul>             </div>         </div>     </div> </div>', 'https://sakos.vn/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/2-14.jpg', 45),
(60, NULL, 'CAT BA BEACH', '<div class=\"beach__body\">\n  <div class=\"beach__about\">\n    <p class=\"beach__about-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">\n      LUSH FORESTS, TRANQUIL BEACHES, AND ADVENTURE GALORE\n    </p>\n    <p class=\"beach__about-text\">\n      Cat Ba Island, part of the UNESCO-recognized Ha Long Bay – Cat Ba Biosphere Reserve, features rugged limestone karsts, dense national park landscapes, and serene beaches like Cat Co and Tung Thu. Visitors can enjoy island hiking, jungle treks, kayaking in Lan Ha Bay, as well as local culture in Cat Ba Town and floating villages. This island balances wild nature and accessible coastal charm perfectly.\n    </p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"beach__image\">\n    <img src=\"https://worlds50beaches.com/assets/images/maps/map-2025-01.jpg\" alt=\"map\">\n  </div>\n</div>', ' <div class=\"container\">     <div class=\"more\">         <div class=\"more__item\">           <p class=\"more__item-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">             CAT BA WEATHER AVERAGES (HAI PHONG CLIMATE)           </p>           <table class=\"weather__table\">             <thead>               <tr>                 <td class=\"first__cell\"></td>                 <td>AVG HIGH (°C)</td>                 <td>AVG LOW (°C)</td>                 <td>RAIN (mm)</td>               </tr>             </thead>             <tbody>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Winter (Dec–Feb)</td><td>20–22</td><td>14–17</td><td>Low</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Spring (Mar–May)</td><td>24–29</td><td>18–22</td><td>Moderate</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Summer (Jun–Aug)</td><td>30–33</td><td>26–28</td><td>High</td></tr>               <tr><td class=\"first__cell\">Autumn (Sep–Nov)</td><td>25–30</td><td>20–24</td><td>Decreasing</td></tr>             </tbody>           </table>        </div>         <div class=\"more__item more__item-right\">           <div class=\"more__info\">             <p class=\"more__info-title\" style=\"text-transform: uppercase;\">               THE PERFECT DAY AT CAT BA BEACH             </p>             <ul class=\"more__info-list\">               <li>                 <p><b>BEST SEASONS</b></p>                 <p>Spring (Mar–May) and Autumn (Sep–Nov) offer mild, dry weather—ideal for hiking, kayaking, and beach time. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>BEACH LOVERS</b></p>                 <p>April to June gives perfect beach weather (24–29 °C, low rain) for swimming and snorkeling. :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>PEAK SUMMER</b></p>                 <p>June–August brings sun and vibrant beach scene (30–33 °C), with occasional storms—plan early beach days. :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}</p>               </li>               <li>                 <p><b>OFF-PEAK TRANQUILITY</b></p>                 <p>Late November offers calm seas, cool temps (20–25 °C), and clear visibility—ideal for cruises. :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}</p>               </li>             </ul>           </div>         </div>     </div> </div>', 'https://catbaexpress.com/upload/img/flamingo-cat-ba-beach-resort.jpg', 46);

